    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset represents a 12-dimensional monthly time series with two quantitative variables (purchases/sales). Synthetic data follows retail patterns: Purchases show linear growth (\u03bc=15.8, \u03c3=7.3) with holiday season acceleration, while sales exhibit parabolic distribution (\u03bc=11.3, \u03c3=4.1) peaking in summer months. Data integrity was maintained through constrained random walks with domain-typical volatility. The dotplot was selected for its ability to show exact counts through stacked markers while maintaining Tufte's data density principles. Cairo's preattentive processing is leveraged through shape-color dual encoding (green squares vs red diamonds), with proportional scaling maintaining accurate magnitude perception. Diverging color scheme supports quick positive/negative balance assessment while avoiding non-semantic hue variation. Statistical anchors include Q4 purchase acceleration (+12% MoM growth) and summer sales peak (June-August comprising 38% of annual sales)."
